Sentinel Burp

A plugin for current versions of burp. 
Eases discovery of common security holes in web applications.

Blog: http://dobin.github.io/
Wiki: https://github.com/dobin/BurpSentinel/wiki

BurpSentinel is a little GUI based Burp extension, which quick and easy can attack
parameters of HTTP requests. 

Features:
- Predefined attack payloads
- Automated identification of reflected XSS
- Automated identification of non-blind SQL injections
- Indicators and visual aid for the user to identify blind/fullblind SQL injections
- UI features for helping the penetration tester


What it cannot do:
- Find DOM Injections
- Exploit vulnerabilities


Alternatives:
- Ironwasp (www.ironwasp.org, .NET)
- Wfuzz (www.edge-security.com/wfuzz.php, Python)